a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.0bfdf343-e763-4227-9dd0-ec8107521513.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null. 
Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.40bf72dc-ab20-44b4-b123-dc43e4ae4412.description=
Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.4511f72f-076a-4aa3-b765-37aa9f57c698.callout=This flow will search a list for a specific value, and return two lists corresponding to the content matches and the corresponding index values. a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.467ef8df-1777-4756-98d7-b5600b53dc82.description=
Gets a list of one or more Elements in a list that match a given filter.

Inputs\:
list - the list to search.
delimiter - The delimiter that separates elements in list.
compareTo - The string to compare each element in the list against.
matchType - The type of match to perform.

Responses\:
success - 1 or more elements were found that matched.
failure - no elements matched, or something went wrong.

Returns\:
A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.

Results\:
others - all elements that did not match
matches - A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.
a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.6d1cd272-c531-4c06-900c-b3c1d23159f2.description=
Returns the length of the list.

Inputs\:
delimiter - The list delimiter.
list - The list to be processed

Responses\:
success - The operation completed Successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
The length of the list.
a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.79bcd13b-1065-46b2-829e-bfe31c1950f7.description=
Counts from one number to another number.

Inputs\:
from - The number to start counting at
to - The number to count to
incrementBy - The amount to increment by during each count.
reset - If set to true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.
a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.7d4a19a0-cf90-4ac6-acca-86a980aaf061.description=
Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.
a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.bf9daadc-43cf-48aa-bc34-ac15b17e1514.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.d02486b2-6f46-40d5-9120-960e7d4f4416.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
a6be37c1-b0e6-41a5-8b0b-1672fe5fa2b2.description=Questions And Suggestions Can Be Forwarded To\: E-DEngineeringApplications@savvis.net Additional Documentation May Be Found At\: Confluence-Engineering Public Documentation \#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\# \#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\#\# \# General Information \# 
Description\:
	This flow will search a list for a specific value, and return two lists corresponding to the content matches and the
	corresponding index values.
Inputs\:
	list		List of Values used to compare the matching value to
	delimiter		List delimiter
	compareTo		Matching value used in comparison with 'list'
	matchType		Method of Match used to determine the success of the comparison
Responses\:
	success		Comparison completed successfully
	failure		Something went wrong
Returns\:
	indexes		List of index values for matching 'list' values
	matches		List of content values for matching 'list' values
	other		List of content values for all non-matching 'list' values
Notes\:
	N/A
